‘This is very big,’ he said. ‘I hope I can show off a lot of the same things I have been show ing.

‘I had not really expected this. I have no rush to play in the senior team.’

Norway boss Per-Mathias Hogmo confirmed Odegaard will win his first cap in the friendly.

‘I said before the season start that Martin could stand for this year’s breakthrough, so this does not surprise me,’ he said. ‘The fact that he is at this level is very special.

